<MarkdownLayout title="Delete Your Data" description="How to delete your data from Carpe!">
  <p>Carpe! is local-first and does not require a general-purpose remote user account for core functionality. Data is stored on your device unless you explicitly export it.</p>

  <h2>Delete all app data in Carpe!</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open <strong>Carpe!</strong></li>
    <li>From the home screen, tap the <strong>Delete account</strong> button in the top bar</li>
    <li>Review the warning dialog</li>
    <li>Tap <strong>Continue</strong> to remove all local app data from the device</li>
  </ol>

  <p>This action removes locally stored databases, records, automation metadata, and associated integrity records from the device. This action cannot be reversed.</p>

  <h2>Delete the app from your device</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open your device settings</li>
    <li>Locate <strong>Carpe!</strong> in installed apps</li>
    <li>Delete the app from the device</li>
  </ol>

  <p>Deleting the app may also remove any remaining locally stored data that has not already been removed through the in-app delete flow.</p>

  <h2>Questions?</h2>
  <p>If you need help, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@mail.provable.dev">contact@mail.provable.dev</a>.</p>
</MarkdownLayout>
